<item>
            <title>[SOLR-95] simplification of solr_server.rb</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-95</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;solr_start() was using a system call to start solr, which resulted in three separate processes that needed to be killed with a process group id. This required solr_start() to disassociate itself from the parent process with setsid, and lookup the subprocesses&apos; parent id.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;using exec() instead of system() makes this complexity go away fortunately. Also the solr_server.rb was renamed to test_helper.rb as it is likely to contain other methods/classes for clearing the index, etc...&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
